    "body": "The [documentation](https://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/generated/pandas.DataFrame.to_csv.html) is very clear on this:\r\n\r\n\"A string representing the encoding to use in the **OUTPUT FILE**, defaults to â€˜asciiâ€™ on Python 2 and â€˜utf-8â€™ on Python 3.\"\r\n\r\nWe never mention support for buffers in general, so I disagree that this is deceptive.  That being said, an attempt to enhance support of `encoding` for non-file objects would be welcomed."
